            <p class="blog-lead">
                If you process invoices manually — copying vendor names, amounts,
                and line items into a spreadsheet — you're spending hours every week
                on work that AI can do in seconds.
            </p>

            <h2>The problem with manual invoice processing</h2>
            <p>
                Most accounting teams still copy invoice data by hand. Someone opens
                a PDF, reads the vendor name, types it into Excel, finds the total,
                types that in, then hunts for the line items. For one invoice it takes
                3-5 minutes. For 50 invoices a week, that's 4+ hours of pure data entry.
            </p>
            <p>
                It's also error-prone. Transposing numbers, missing line items,
                wrong dates — these mistakes cause real problems come reconciliation time.
            </p>

            <h2>How AI invoice extraction works</h2>
            <p>
                Modern AI tools like PdfToolStack's invoice extractor use large language
                models to read PDF text the same way a human would — understanding context,
                not just pattern-matching. Upload an invoice and the AI identifies:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Vendor name and address</li>
                <li>Invoice number and date</li>
                <li>Due date and payment terms</li>
                <li>Line items with descriptions, quantities, and unit prices</li>
                <li>Subtotal, tax, and total amounts</li>
                <li>Purchase order references</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                All of this is then exported to a structured Excel file — one row per
                invoice, or a detailed sheet with line items broken out.
            </p>

            <h2>Step-by-step: Extract invoice data with AI</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Go to <a href="/extract-invoice-data">PdfToolStack Invoice Extractor</a></li>
                <li>Select <strong>Invoice</strong> as the document type</li>
                <li>Upload your PDF invoice (up to 50MB)</li>
                <li>Click <strong>Extract Data with AI</strong></li>
                <li>Review the extracted fields on screen</li>
                <li>Download the Excel file</li>
            </ol>
            <p>
                The whole process takes under 30 seconds for a standard invoice.
            </p>

            <h2>What types of invoices does it work on?</h2>
            <p>
                The AI works on any text-based PDF invoice — whether it was created
                in Word, QuickBooks, FreshBooks, Xero, or any other software. It also
                handles invoices exported from accounting systems, emailed PDFs, and
                supplier invoices in various formats.
            </p>
            <p>
                For scanned invoices — physical invoices that were photographed or
                faxed — you'll need to run OCR first to make the text readable,
                then extract. PdfToolStack has a built-in
                <a href="/pdf-ocr">PDF OCR tool</a> for exactly this.
            </p>

